thread.title_full: Murphy, Mets sweep Cubs to roll into World Series

title: Murphy, Mets sweep Cubs to roll into World Series
text: Murphy, Mets sweep Cubs to roll into World Series Oct. 21, 2015 Updated 8:57 p.m. 1 of 16 The Mets' Daniel Murphy hits a single during the fourth inning of Game 4 against the Mets. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs pitcher Jason Hammel sits in the dugout after being knocked out of the game during the second inning of Game 4 against the Mets. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Daniel Murphy (28) and David Wright celebrate after scoring on a double by Lucas Duda during the second inning of Game 4 against the Cubs. DAVID GOLDMAN, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Lucas Duda, center, is congratulated by Yoenis Cespedes, left, and Curtis Granderson, right, after hitting a three-run home run during the first inning of Game 4 against the Cubs. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Lucas Duda watches his three-run home run along with Cubs pitcher Jason Hammel during the first inning of Game 4 on Wednesday. DAVID GOLDMAN, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Travis d'Arnaud crosses the plate after hitting a home run during the first inning of Game 4 against the Cubs. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs pitcher Jason Hammel wipe his face after being relieved during the second inning of Game 4 of the National League Championship Series against the Mets on Wednesday. NAM Y. HUH, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Curtis Granderson steals second with the Cubs' Starlin Castro covering during the first inning of Game 4. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Curtis Granderson reacts as he scores during the first inning of Game 4 against the Cubs. ELSA, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 The Mets' Lucas Duda hits a two-run double during the second inning of Game 4 against the Cubs. DAVID GOLDMAN, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs left fielder Kyle Schwarber can't catch a ball hit by the Mets' Wilmer Flores during the first inning of Game 4. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs left fielder Kyle Schwarber can't catch a ball hit by the Mets' Wilmer Flores during the first inning of Game 4 on Wednesday. CHARLES REX ARBOGAST, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs left fielder Kyle Schwarber misplays a fly ball in the first inning against the Mets during Game 4 on Wednesday. NUCCIO DINUZZO, CHICAGO TRIBUNE/TNS 1 of 16 The Cubs' Javier Baez tags out Mets runner Wilmer Flores as he is caught stealing second during the third inning of Game 4. CHARLES REX ARBOGAST, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs catcher David Ross walks off the field thinking the inning was over but there were only two strikes on the Mets' Steven Matz during the third inning. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 16 Cubs fans watch with their team trailing the Mets 6-0 during the fourth inning of Game 4 on Wednesday. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS The Mets' Daniel Murphy hits a single during the fourth inning of Game 4 against the Mets. DAVID J. PHILLIP, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS By THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
